Feiler Family 2021/22
The following represents somewhat of a departure from the usual clever, witty, incredibly interesting yearly
novel of Feiler family happenings. Life has slowed down a bit so the effort this year (covering two years)
presented in an abbreviated format. Our family composition at this time is Louise and me, four sons, three
daughter-in-loves, and six grandchildren age ranging from 2 months to 19 years. Precious are the times we
have spent with them. We have loved our long-distance family visits mainly to/fro the Pahrump and San
Diego gangs. The local folks (Matthew, and Luke, Lauren, Isla, and now brand new (18 Nov) Emery Joy), we
see very frequently. Except for COVID, life for Louise and me continues at a very pleasant rate.
Pahrump group. John: now for many years, working as
a mill wright at the Nevada Test Site keeping his eyes
open for other opportunities; working on the 3
rd
novel
of the Junctionworld trilogy. Now 19, John “Little” Bear
(6’4”) graduated high school in 2021, moved in with us
in Fall 2022 to attend college here in Reno; welcomed
him to Reno by taking him to the Hot Air Balloon
Festival, the Reno Air Races, etc ; he is doing well
(straight A’s the first semester). Olivia, now a high
school junior and doing well, racking up her driving
hours required for legal behind-the-wheel solo trips.
San Diego group. Mark/Keri: continue to make some
very incredible improvements to their house and
property, quite the plant gurus, and now the owners of
four egg-producing chickens. Mia, in a Spanish immersion
school, excelling in piano, soccer, etc. We spent a month
with them helping out as Mark recovered from some toe
surgery. Mark continues employment with the city
maintaining community swimming pools; Keri continues
as nurse in the NICU department. Firecracker Jude got his
first haircut, but retains his strength and exuberance.
Matthew shifted from barista
employment and now enjoys his Costco
employment. He continues to execute audio/video
duties at our church.
Luke and Lauren added to their family with the
joyous birth of Emery Joy Feiler last month (18 Nov
2022). Luke works water safety engineering duties
with Hughes (requiring a bit more travel as the
west coast “guy”); Lauren, enjoying three months
of maternity leave, before returning as nurse in
pediatric oncology. Isla Rose, now two, is a weekly babysitting enjoyment
we heartily cherish.
Constants keep our
life fairly steady and
predictable to
include frequent
church activities, Isla
babysitting, one to
two visits/week
caring for my 92-
year-old step-father
(Dale Holmes), skiing
4-5 days per year, 8-
game yearly passes
for our local Reno
Aces minor league
baseball team (feeds
the Arizona
Diamondbacks) . . . .
We both tested
positive to COVID
but given our
vaccinations, our
symptoms were very
minor. We’ve had our fair share of medical events to include big events of cataract eye surgery for Louise and
a Total Knee Replacement of my other knee (right knee in Sep 2020, left in May 2022). We scheduled our
medical issues so we could tackle a major effort of replacing wall to wall carpet with wood flooring.
We love living in Reno and enjoy the four seasons,
although it seems like “Fall” lasts only a couple weeks. We
had a 14” snow dump (at our house) in early December
with much greater depths in the mountain ski resorts (I got
one day in already). God has blessed us with over 38 years
of wedded bliss!!!!!
